                "text": "15 feet. The fuming sludge constantly emits incendiary smoke that creates <a aonid=\"4\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">concealment</a> around it. The smoke doesn't impair the fuming sludge's chemical sense. A creature that enters the aura or begins its turn in the aura becomes <a aonid=\"34\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">sickened 1</a> DC 25 Fortitude negates) and cannot recover from <a aonid=\"29\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">persistent fire damage</a> for 1 round. It is then temporarily immune to the sickening effect of the smoldering haze for 1 minute. A creature that is currently holding its breath, that doesn't need to breathe, or that's immune to <a aonid=\"126\" game-obj=\"Traits\">poison</a> is immune to the aura's sickened effect but not the concealment or inability to recover from persistent fire damage."
            }
